stylometry: @RISK output purpose is to keep track of the profit and in doing so we designate the profit cell as the output cell.  The function indicated that a cell is an output cell in order for @RISK to keep track of its value during the entire simulation.  Things that it shows you are when you run the simulation it will bring up a report that will show you the results and you then determine which is the best to choose.When making a decision on how many calenders to order you are looking for the best order quantity that will give you the highest mean profit and lowest standard deviation.
